pective on the history of St. Petersburg on the eve of revolution and presents a fresh view of Russia's experience of modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCity and town lifexHistoryxRussia (Federation)xSaint Petersburg. 0aCity and town lifezRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 0aModernism (Aesthetics)xHistoryxRussia (Federation)xSaint Petersburg. 0aModernism (Aesthetics)zRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 0aPopular culturexHistoryxRussia (Federation)xSaint Petersburg. 0aPopular culturezRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 0aSocial changexHistoryxRussia (Federation)xSaint Petersburg. 0aSocial changezRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 0aSocial problemsxHistoryxRussia (Federation)xSaint Petersburg. 0aSocial problemszRussia (Federation)zSaint PetersburgxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300165708423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300165708.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles